    "created_at": "2015-01-17T01:33:45Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-01-17T01:33:45Z",
    "body": "Would you still get some benefits by specifying the universe of crates from the get-go, without writing that problematic blob of metadata to disk? It would simplify rustdoc's rendering of cross-crate trait impls and generating a search index I suppose.\n",
